4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would create an additional incentive
6 program within the Alabama Entertainment Office by
7 allowing small productions with production expenditures
8 of $100,000-$499,999 to qualify for an incentive rebate
9 for 45 percent of all production payroll paid to
10 residents of Alabama.
11 This bill would extend the deadline for the
12 Department of Commerce to contract with an out-of-state
13 entity to review and evaluate incentives as prescribed
14 by the Entertainment Industry Incentive Act of 2009 and
15 report the findings to the Legislature on the 1st
16 legislative day of the 2028 Regular Legislative
17 Session.
18 This bill would also clarify requirements for
19 including compensation paid to loan out companies for
20 purposes of calculating the rebate under Section
21 41-7A-43.
22
23
